        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I currently wear Terrorclaw's hide, but have all my trade skills high enough to get shawl 8 (just need to farm components).  The pieces from West Wastes in particular are rather rare...  My suggestion to you is to put Shawl 8 on the back burner for now... worry about it when you're 60.  Terrorclaw Hide is fantastic and will serve you well up until then.</P><P>Shawl 8 would be an excellent goal for the long run... you'll get approximately 65 hp (slightly less than terrorclaw) but also get FT 2.  While FT 2 on its own is not significant.. when stacked with PoTC earring, FT3 boots, and MC 3, you're totalling up to Flowing Thought 9 (an extra 5400 mana regen'ed every hour).</P><P>Short answer.. stick with terrorclaw for now, and I'd recommend that you work towards Shawl 8 when you're 60 if you feel like it.</P><P>Borael<BR>Gnome Warlock</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
