        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Robes and pants, inexplicably, or perhaps not so inexplicably, since the effects on robe and pants for all casters seem pretty sweet, seem to be very rare, especially in Kael. In HoT the robe drops fairly regularly (I got one as an applicant to my guild, and we had a few drop in one day) and in ToV (the Kael robe) they drop fairly regularly also.</P><P>With the shoulder piece issues, personally, 10% mana conservation, when you are regenning mana evilly fast, don't really mean a lot. I'd get it if I had a slot free and the stats on the item were really decent, but at 60, I would pick the Terrorclaws (It's what I'm wearing now) over the OBS. The shawl is nice if you can pull it, the FT2 isn't the most wonderful for necromancers, but hey, it's something. I wouldn't sacrifice a much better stat item for it however.</P><P>Sometimes I wish I had a little FT item for when I'm running someplace and not quite FM, coz then I can just run regaining a lil mana as I go. Not really that fun to run while you are Liching and all :) It's also nice when you have had to FD from a bad pull and you can't afford to leave Lich on.</P><P>However, I would look at 1, raw HP and mana, 2, INT (especially this order if you have a high base INT, like an Erudite or Dark Elf or Gnome) 3, resists, then other effects like focus effects and FT. If you find a nice item which has a good balance of these, go to it :)</P><P>Saminga Amaranth, 60th Bad Girl of Avatars of Discord, Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
