        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         1-10% mana off all your spells, after spec check.  Yeah thats a POS alright.  Are you a well trained necro?  If by well trained you mean an arrogant prick, then yeah you got that down.</P><P>How much mana saved is MP3?  No idea, but average of about 5% off every casting.</P><P>So, if you are casting 1000mana/min  (which isnt a lot) you are saving the equivalent of what FT5 would regen for you in the same amount of time.  Now granted, its not always on like an FT item is.  But still, its a nice savings and something that works for you more often than adding mana/hp to the bottom of your pool.</P><P>Measure that against the Terrorclaw, which adds what, about 100 mana/hp?  Which is better?  Normally my priority is HPs, but they are only coming into play when you are close to death, which frankly I am not most of the EQ day.  The benefits of the ODS are going to affect you a whole hell of a lot more often than those of the Terrorclaw.  8th shawl is overall better than both I think, but its a hell of a lot more work to get as well.</P><P>If I had an AE3 item, I would ditch the ODS for the Terrorclaw.  But I dont.  Or, if the effect on the Terroclaw was somthing useful, like Arch-Lich or AoD, I would ditch the ODS because it would like gaining a spell slot.</P><P>Sayleth</P><P>And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8</P><P>edit: Terrorclaw only about 75hp/mana, not 100.  Less than I thought.</P><P>Edited by - Sayleth on 08/06/2002  10:50:05<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
