         I ended up getting a warlock's robe MQ from a guildie after I'd been 60 for a good long while.  Never saw the thing drop and I spent a decent ammount of time in Kael.  I wouldn't count on getting that on a raid but I hear MQs sell for only 15k or so on our server so that's pretty cheap for an item with stats like that.  Thurg is the best, too, imo.  10svm.</P><P>And, about the shoulder item, camp master yael and get a strength of the elements.  I look at it like this.  I only have like 3200 mana right now.  10% would make those shoulders roughly 320 mana to me and shitty stats otherwise.  Would I rather have 320 mana or 100 health and 15sv cold and fire?  I'd rather have the health and saves.  Good saves on good gear is premo.  I'd never wear an ods.  320 mana dosn't mean that much to me.  Nice health + saves on the same item > everything.  I wouldn't give up my strength of the elements for any items that are obtainable without a huge raid effort if you can even find the stuff up.  <img src=icon_smile_tongue.gif border=0 align=middle>  I think there is ONE item outside of vex thal that I'd consider an upgrade.  The only way I'd sacrifice health and saves is if the ods had some regen on it, too.  As regen is almost as good as health.  Better, sometimes.</P><P>Screw ods.  Screw mana.  Scm3 is good 'nuff for me.  And, I got lich.  Dosn't everyone else?</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
